package main

// houseCuspText holds specific interpretations for every house-cusp-in-sign combo.
// Key format: "House_Sign" (e.g. "1_Aries", "10_Capricorn")
var houseCuspText = map[string]string{

	// ── HOUSE 1 ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"1_Aries":       "With the cusp of your First House in Aries, you approach the world with directness, confidence, and an instinct to initiate. The way you assert yourself and build your identity is colored by Aries' bold, independent energy. You are at your best when forging your own path — and you tend to make your presence felt the moment you walk into a room.",
	"1_Taurus":      "With the cusp of your First House in Taurus, your sense of self is grounded, patient, and deeply rooted in the physical world. You build your identity slowly and deliberately, preferring steady accumulation of experience over sudden leaps. Others perceive you as calm, reliable, and aesthetically attuned — someone whose presence feels solid and reassuring.",
	"1_Gemini":      "With the cusp of your First House in Gemini, your self-expression is quick, curious, and versatile. You come across as communicative, mentally engaged, and adaptable — someone who can shift registers easily and who is always collecting new impressions and ideas. Your identity is partly defined by your relationship to language and information.",
	"1_Cancer":      "With the cusp of your First House in Cancer, your self-expression is emotionally attuned, protective, and shaped by your inner feeling life. Your sense of identity is closely tied to your roots, your family, and your need for emotional security. Others may perceive you as sensitive, nurturing, and somewhat private — someone whose depth reveals itself gradually.",
	"1_Leo":         "With the cusp of your First House in Leo, your self-expression is warm, confident, and naturally expressive. You come across as someone who shines — whose presence brings color and vitality to any room. Your identity is inseparable from your need to be fully, authentically yourself, and you bring a creative, generous quality to everything you do.",
	"1_Virgo":       "With the cusp of your First House in Virgo, your self-expression is precise, observant, and oriented toward improvement. You come across as intelligent, capable, and quietly perceptive — someone who pays attention to what others miss. Your identity is shaped by your relationship to work, craft, and the desire to be genuinely, practically useful.",
	"1_Libra":       "With the cusp of your First House in Libra, your self-expression is gracious, diplomatic, and aesthetically refined. You come across as charming, fair-minded, and socially adept — someone who makes others feel comfortable and seen. Your identity is significantly shaped by your relationships and your need for harmony and beauty in your environment.",
	"1_Scorpio":     "With the cusp of your First House in Scorpio, your self-expression is intense, controlled, and magnetic. You come across as someone of depth and power — others sense there is much more beneath the surface than you reveal. Your identity is shaped by your relationship to transformation, psychological truth, and the parts of life that most people prefer to avoid.",
	"1_Sagittarius": "With the cusp of your First House in Sagittarius, your self-expression is enthusiastic, expansive, and oriented toward freedom and meaning. You come across as open, direct, and energetically optimistic — someone who makes others feel that life is full of possibility. Your identity is shaped by your beliefs, your love of adventure, and your need for a horizon worth pursuing.",
	"1_Capricorn":   "With the cusp of your First House in Capricorn, your self-expression is composed, serious, and characterized by a quiet, earned authority. You come across as disciplined, reliable, and capable — someone whose patience and competence inspire confidence. Your identity is shaped by your ambitions, your relationship to responsibility, and the long work of building something that will endure.",
	"1_Aquarius":    "With the cusp of your First House in Aquarius, your self-expression is original, independent, and unmistakably your own. You come across as intellectually unconventional and somewhat detached — someone who operates on their own terms and refuses to be easily categorized. Your identity is shaped by your values, your vision for the future, and your commitment to being uncompromisingly yourself.",
	"1_Pisces":      "With the cusp of your First House in Pisces, your self-expression is fluid, empathic, and difficult to pin down. You come across as sensitive, imaginative, and somewhat mysterious — someone whose presence has a dreamlike, changeable quality. Your identity is shaped by your inner life, your spiritual sensibility, and your profound attunement to the emotional atmosphere around you.",

	// ── HOUSE 2 ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"2_Aries":       "With the cusp of your Second House in Aries, you approach money and material resources with boldness, initiative, and a willingness to take financial risks. You tend to earn through your own independent efforts and may pursue income with a competitive edge. Financial patience can be a challenge — you may act impulsively around money — but your drive generates real earning power when channeled well.",
	"2_Taurus":      "With the cusp of your Second House in Taurus, your relationship with money and material resources is stable, patient, and pleasure-oriented. Taurus governs this house naturally — you have a genuine gift for building and holding material security, and you are drawn to quality, beauty, and comfort in what you own. Your financial security comes from steady accumulation rather than speculation.",
	"2_Gemini":      "With the cusp of your Second House in Gemini, your income and material resources tend to come through communication, information, or intellectual skills. You may have multiple income streams or a variable relationship with money that reflects Gemini's dual nature. Your financial life benefits from diversification, and you are at your most resourceful when your earning capacity is connected to your mind.",
	"2_Cancer":      "With the cusp of your Second House in Cancer, your sense of material security is deeply emotional — you feel safe when you have resources to protect yourself and your loved ones. You may earn through nurturing, caregiving, or home-related work. Comfort and the feeling of being provided for are as important to your financial wellbeing as the actual numbers in your account.",
	"2_Leo":         "With the cusp of your Second House in Leo, your relationship with money and resources is generous, proud, and oriented toward quality and status. You may earn through creative work, leadership, or performance, and you are not afraid to spend lavishly on the things you value. Financial abundance feels like an expression of your identity, and you take genuine pride in your capacity to provide.",
	"2_Virgo":       "With the cusp of your Second House in Virgo, your approach to money and material resources is practical, analytical, and carefully managed. You tend to be a diligent earner and a thoughtful spender, with a keen eye for value and an ability to make the most of modest resources. Sound, meticulous management is your greatest financial gift.",
	"2_Libra":       "With the cusp of your Second House in Libra, your relationship with money is connected to beauty, balance, and the quality of your partnerships. You may earn through creative, aesthetic, or socially oriented work, and you tend to share resources generously and expect fairness in return. Financial harmony in your close relationships is important to your overall sense of security.",
	"2_Scorpio":     "With the cusp of your Second House in Scorpio, your relationship with material resources is intense, strategic, and capable of profound transformation. You may experience significant financial highs and lows, but you have an extraordinary capacity to regenerate your resources after loss. You tend to hold your financial situation closely and privately, and you earn through Scorpionic fields — investment, research, or healing.",
	"2_Sagittarius": "With the cusp of your Second House in Sagittarius, your relationship with money is expansive, optimistic, and sometimes overextended. You tend to attract abundance when living in alignment with your beliefs, and you may earn through philosophical, educational, or travel-related work. Financial planning can be challenging — your natural inclination is toward abundance thinking rather than careful budgeting.",
	"2_Capricorn":   "With the cusp of your Second House in Capricorn, your approach to money and material resources is serious, disciplined, and long-term. You build financial security slowly and methodically through sustained effort and sound planning. The financial security you build tends to be solid and enduring — the kind that accumulates over decades rather than arriving in a sudden windfall.",
	"2_Aquarius":    "With the cusp of your Second House in Aquarius, your relationship with money and resources is unconventional and subject to sudden change. You may earn through innovative, technology-oriented, or humanitarian work, and your financial life tends to be less predictable than most. Your financial decisions are as likely to be guided by your values and ideals as by practical considerations.",
	"2_Pisces":      "With the cusp of your Second House in Pisces, your relationship with money and material resources is fluid, idealistic, and sometimes difficult to manage concretely. You may experience abundance and scarcity in cycles, and you have a tendency to give generously without a clear accounting of what remains. Developing a grounded, practical relationship with money while maintaining your natural generosity is the challenge and the work.",

	// ── HOUSE 3 ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"3_Aries":       "With the cusp of your Third House in Aries, your communication style is direct, fast, and unafraid of confrontation. You say what you mean without much hedging, and your mind moves quickly from thought to expression. Siblings and neighbors may be energetic or competitive presences in your life, and your local environment tends to be active and stimulating.",
	"3_Taurus":      "With the cusp of your Third House in Taurus, your communication style is measured, deliberate, and grounded. You take your time forming and expressing ideas, preferring substance over speed. Your mind operates through the senses — you learn best through hands-on experience, and your speech carries a steady, reliable quality that makes others trust what you say.",
	"3_Gemini":      "With the cusp of your Third House in Gemini, the house is in its natural sign — your communication style is quick, versatile, and intellectually energized. You are comfortable with multiple streams of information simultaneously, and you express yourself with ease and adaptability. Writing, speaking, and the exchange of ideas are areas of genuine natural ability.",
	"3_Cancer":      "With the cusp of your Third House in Cancer, your communication style is emotionally attuned, personal, and shaped by feeling as much as by logic. You communicate best when you feel emotionally safe, and your words carry a warmth and memory-rich quality. Your relationship with siblings and your early learning environment was likely shaped by strong emotional currents.",
	"3_Leo":         "With the cusp of your Third House in Leo, your communication style is warm, dramatic, and expressive. You speak with confidence and a natural flair that makes others pay attention, and you have a gift for storytelling and performance. Your local environment and everyday interactions tend to be venues for creative self-expression and personal recognition.",
	"3_Virgo":       "With the cusp of your Third House in Virgo, your communication style is precise, analytical, and oriented toward accuracy and usefulness. You choose your words carefully and notice when others use them loosely. Your mind is naturally suited to editing, research, writing, and any work that requires careful attention to the details of language and information.",
	"3_Libra":       "With the cusp of your Third House in Libra, your communication style is diplomatic, balanced, and aesthetically refined. You have a natural talent for seeing multiple sides and expressing yourself with tact and grace. Your local environment and relationships with siblings and neighbors tend to be pleasant and harmonious, and you may be a natural mediator in everyday conflicts.",
	"3_Scorpio":     "With the cusp of your Third House in Scorpio, your communication style is penetrating, strategic, and often deliberately selective. You say less than you know, and what you do say tends to carry weight. Your mind is naturally drawn to research, investigation, and the hidden dimensions of whatever subject interests you. Your early environment may have involved significant psychological complexity.",
	"3_Sagittarius": "With the cusp of your Third House in Sagittarius, your communication style is expansive, enthusiastic, and oriented toward the big picture. You are a natural storyteller and teacher, and you tend to communicate in a way that opens things up rather than narrows them down. Short journeys and everyday learning often carry a philosophical or adventurous quality for you.",
	"3_Capricorn":   "With the cusp of your Third House in Capricorn, your communication style is serious, authoritative, and economical. You prefer to say what is necessary and say it well, rather than speaking at length. Your mind works methodically and carefully, and you have a talent for communicating complex ideas with clarity and structural precision.",
	"3_Aquarius":    "With the cusp of your Third House in Aquarius, your communication style is original, ahead of its time, and sometimes deliberately unconventional. You enjoy challenging the assumptions behind how things are talked about and thought about, and your mind tends to produce genuinely novel ideas. Your local network is likely to be diverse, progressive, and intellectually stimulating.",
	"3_Pisces":      "With the cusp of your Third House in Pisces, your communication style is imaginative, empathic, and infused with feeling. You may communicate most powerfully through creative writing, music, or other forms that bypass purely rational expression. Your mind absorbs impressions more than facts, and your relationship with information is more intuitive than linear.",

	// ── HOUSE 4 ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"4_Aries":       "With the cusp of your Fourth House in Aries, your home life and psychological foundations are energized by assertiveness, independence, and sometimes conflict. Your private self is bold and self-determining — you need your home to be a place where you have real autonomy. Your family background may have included strong, competitive personalities, and you have developed a fierce inner independence as a result.",
	"4_Taurus":      "With the cusp of your Fourth House in Taurus, your home life and psychological foundations are grounded, sensory, and deeply connected to physical comfort and stability. You need your home to be beautiful, well-provisioned, and genuinely yours. Your roots run deep in the material and sensory world, and your sense of security is built on the bedrock of reliable physical comfort.",
	"4_Gemini":      "With the cusp of your Fourth House in Gemini, your home life and psychological foundations are animated by communication, intellectual activity, and variety. You may have grown up in an environment where words, ideas, and movement were central. Your private self is mentally active even in rest, and you may find that your home life involves more change and variety than most.",
	"4_Cancer":      "With the cusp of your Fourth House in Cancer, the Moon's natural home — your home life and psychological foundations are deeply emotional, nurturing, and family-oriented. Your roots are among your most powerful sources of both strength and challenge. A genuine sense of home and belonging is essential to your wellbeing, and your private life may be your most important life.",
	"4_Leo":         "With the cusp of your Fourth House in Leo, your home life and psychological foundations are animated by warmth, creativity, and a need for your private self to be celebrated and recognized. Your home is your stage in some fundamental sense — the place where your truest self is most fully expressed. You may have grown up in a household where performance, pride, and individuality were important.",
	"4_Virgo":       "With the cusp of your Fourth House in Virgo, your home life and psychological foundations are shaped by the desire for order, usefulness, and a sense that everything is properly attended to. Your private self is more critical and self-demanding than you may let on in public. Home functions best for you when it is clean, organized, and purposeful.",
	"4_Libra":       "With the cusp of your Fourth House in Libra, your home life and psychological foundations are shaped by the desire for beauty, harmony, and balanced relationship. Your private self is more relationally oriented than you may appear publicly — you need your home to be aesthetically pleasing and interpersonally peaceful to feel genuinely at ease. Conflict at home is unusually destabilizing for you.",
	"4_Scorpio":     "With the cusp of your Fourth House in Scorpio, your home life and psychological foundations are deep, intense, and sometimes shadowed by unspoken power dynamics or family secrets. Your private self is psychologically complex, and the hidden currents of your family history run strongly through your emotional makeup. Over time, your greatest work is transforming your roots rather than simply inheriting them.",
	"4_Sagittarius": "With the cusp of your Fourth House in Sagittarius, your home life and psychological foundations are shaped by a love of freedom, philosophical exploration, and the sense of the world as a larger home than any single place. You may have grown up in a family with strong philosophical convictions or in an environment marked by travel and cultural diversity. Home, for you, is wherever your spirit feels free.",
	"4_Capricorn":   "With the cusp of your Fourth House in Capricorn, your home life and psychological foundations are shaped by discipline, structure, and the weight of responsibility. You may have grown up in a household where authority, duty, and achievement were central values. Your private self is more serious and self-demanding than you reveal publicly, and you build your home life with the same steady, methodical approach you bring to your career.",
	"4_Aquarius":    "With the cusp of your Fourth House in Aquarius, your home life and psychological foundations are unconventional, freedom-oriented, and resistant to traditional domestic patterns. You may have grown up in an unusual or progressive family environment, and your private life continues to follow its own original rules. Home, for you, is a space for intellectual freedom and authenticity rather than comfort in any conventional sense.",
	"4_Pisces":      "With the cusp of your Fourth House in Pisces, your home life and psychological foundations are infused with imagination, spiritual sensitivity, and emotional fluidity. Your private self is deeply compassionate and porous — you absorb the emotional atmosphere of your home environment profoundly. Your roots may be marked by idealization, loss, or spiritual depth, and your innermost sanctuary is ultimately a place of the spirit.",

	// ── HOUSE 5 ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"5_Aries":       "With the cusp of your Fifth House in Aries, you pursue pleasure, romance, and creative expression with directness and enthusiasm. You fall in love quickly and passionately, and your creative energy is vigorous and action-oriented. You are at your most joyful when you are competing, creating, or pursuing something new with unbridled enthusiasm.",
	"5_Taurus":      "With the cusp of your Fifth House in Taurus, your approach to pleasure, romance, and creativity is sensual, patient, and oriented toward lasting beauty. You take your time falling in love and prefer relationships that have a solid, dependable quality. Your creative expression tends toward the physical and aesthetic — music, art, cooking, or any craft that engages the senses.",
	"5_Gemini":      "With the cusp of your Fifth House in Gemini, your approach to pleasure, romance, and creativity is playful, curious, and mentally stimulating. You are attracted to partners who are intellectually engaging, and your creative expression thrives when it involves language, ideas, and variety. Your love life tends to be lively and communicative, and you may have multiple creative interests running simultaneously.",
	"5_Cancer":      "With the cusp of your Fifth House in Cancer, your approach to pleasure, romance, and creativity is emotionally deep and protective. You fall in love with your whole heart, and your creative work is nourished by emotional memory and a deep attunement to the inner life. Children, if you have them, may be a particularly profound source of joy and creative inspiration.",
	"5_Leo":         "With the cusp of your Fifth House in Leo, the house is in its natural sign — pleasure, romance, and creativity are areas of particular radiance and good fortune for you. You love grandly and express yourself with theatrical generosity. Your creative gifts shine when given a stage, and you have a natural gift for bringing joy and playfulness into the lives of those around you.",
	"5_Virgo":       "With the cusp of your Fifth House in Virgo, your approach to pleasure, romance, and creativity is careful, discerning, and oriented toward craft rather than spontaneity. You may approach creative work with almost perfectionist attention, and you are selective in love — quality matters more to you than quantity. Over time, your creative discipline produces work of real precision and lasting value.",
	"5_Libra":       "With the cusp of your Fifth House in Libra, your approach to pleasure, romance, and creativity is graceful, aesthetically oriented, and deeply relational. You are a natural romantic, drawn to beauty and refinement in love and in art. Your creative expression is most alive in contexts that involve collaboration, aesthetic beauty, or the pursuit of harmony between two people.",
	"5_Scorpio":     "With the cusp of your Fifth House in Scorpio, your approach to pleasure, romance, and creativity is intense, deeply private, and all-or-nothing. You love with an extraordinary depth and transformative power, and your creative work is driven by the need to express what lies beneath the surface of ordinary experience. Your relationship with pleasure is profound rather than casual.",
	"5_Sagittarius": "With the cusp of your Fifth House in Sagittarius, your approach to pleasure, romance, and creativity is adventurous, philosophical, and free-spirited. You are attracted to love affairs that feel like journeys, and to creative work that expands your world. You love with enthusiasm and optimism, and you need a partner and a creative life that keep pointing toward new horizons.",
	"5_Capricorn":   "With the cusp of your Fifth House in Capricorn, your approach to pleasure, romance, and creativity is serious, disciplined, and oriented toward mastery. You may not fall in love easily or play frivolously — your pleasures tend to be earned and your creative work is approached with professional seriousness. Over time, your disciplined creative practice produces work of remarkable endurance and quality.",
	"5_Aquarius":    "With the cusp of your Fifth House in Aquarius, your approach to pleasure, romance, and creativity is unconventional, intellectually charged, and resistant to the ordinary. You are attracted to love that is also genuine friendship — relationships that allow both partners maximum individual freedom. Your creative work tends to be original and ahead of its time.",
	"5_Pisces":      "With the cusp of your Fifth House in Pisces, your approach to pleasure, romance, and creativity is deeply imaginative, compassionate, and spiritually tinged. You fall in love with idealistic intensity, and your creative expression draws from the deepest wells of the unconscious and the spirit. Your most powerful creative work tends to transcend the ordinary, touching something universal.",

	// ── HOUSE 6 ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"6_Aries":       "With the cusp of your Sixth House in Aries, you approach your daily work and health with energy, initiative, and a competitive drive. You work best when acting independently and with a clear sense of urgency. Your health benefits from vigorous physical activity, and you tend to be most productive when your work involves a degree of challenge or fresh initiative.",
	"6_Taurus":      "With the cusp of your Sixth House in Taurus, your approach to daily work and health is steady, methodical, and focused on building something lasting. You are at your best in work environments that allow you to proceed at your own pace without constant interruption. Your health benefits from regular, pleasurable physical routines and a lifestyle that nourishes the senses.",
	"6_Gemini":      "With the cusp of your Sixth House in Gemini, your daily work thrives when it involves communication, variety, and intellectual engagement. You work best in environments that allow for mental agility and variety — repetitive or monotonous work drains you quickly. Stress and nervous tension can manifest physically when your mind is overstimulated.",
	"6_Cancer":      "With the cusp of your Sixth House in Cancer, your daily work and health are deeply connected to your emotional state. You do your best work when you feel emotionally secure and when your work environment has a nurturing, familiar quality. You may be drawn to caregiving professions, and your health benefits from emotional attunement — attending to feelings rather than suppressing them.",
	"6_Leo":         "With the cusp of your Sixth House in Leo, your daily work is most effective when it allows for creative expression, leadership, and a degree of recognition. You bring genuine warmth and creative energy to your work, and you perform best when you feel seen and appreciated. Your health benefits from joy, creative activity, and a work environment that allows your natural vitality to shine.",
	"6_Virgo":       "With the cusp of your Sixth House in Virgo, the house is in its natural sign — your approach to daily work and health is precise, analytical, and dedicated to craft and continuous improvement. You are a meticulous worker with high standards, and your health practices tend to be thoughtful and well-researched. The shadow is perfectionism and a tendency to overwork that depletes rather than builds.",
	"6_Libra":       "With the cusp of your Sixth House in Libra, your daily work is most effective in harmonious, collaborative environments where beauty and balance are valued. Conflict or disorganization in your work environment genuinely affects your efficiency and wellbeing. Your health benefits from balance — moderate, pleasurable routines that avoid excess in either direction.",
	"6_Scorpio":     "With the cusp of your Sixth House in Scorpio, your daily work and health are characterized by intensity, depth, and a capacity for complete, transformative engagement. You work best in roles that allow for deep investigation, significant autonomy, and the sense that what you are doing genuinely matters. Your health may be subject to intense periods of depletion followed by equally powerful regeneration.",
	"6_Sagittarius": "With the cusp of your Sixth House in Sagittarius, your daily work is most effective when it is meaningful, philosophically engaging, and connected to a larger purpose. You work with enthusiasm when you believe in what you are doing and may struggle with work that feels meaningless or overly routine. Your health benefits from freedom, outdoor activity, and a daily life that includes room for exploration and growth.",
	"6_Capricorn":   "With the cusp of your Sixth House in Capricorn, your approach to daily work and health is disciplined, structured, and long-term. You are a reliable and methodical worker who holds yourself to high professional standards. Your health benefits from consistent, structured routines, and you tend to take care of your body with the same practicality and patience you bring to everything else.",
	"6_Aquarius":    "With the cusp of your Sixth House in Aquarius, your approach to daily work and health is unconventional, independent, and oriented toward the novel. You thrive in non-traditional work environments where you have significant autonomy and the freedom to experiment. An innovative, nontraditional approach to wellness tends to work better for you than orthodox regimen.",
	"6_Pisces":      "With the cusp of your Sixth House in Pisces, your daily work and health are deeply influenced by your spiritual and emotional state. You do your best work in environments that are compassionate and not overly rigid. Your health is particularly responsive to emotional and spiritual conditions, and practices such as meditation, creative expression, and time in nature are genuinely restorative.",

	// ── HOUSE 7 ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"7_Aries":       "With the cusp of your Seventh House in Aries, you are drawn to partners who are bold, assertive, and independently motivated. Your close relationships tend to have an energetic, sometimes combative quality — you bring out the fighter in each other. The lesson is learning to channel this competitive energy into productive collaboration rather than recurring conflict.",
	"7_Taurus":      "With the cusp of your Seventh House in Taurus, you are drawn to partners who are grounded, sensual, and reliably steady. You seek a relationship that provides real security and physical comfort, and you approach partnership with patience and loyalty. Once committed, you are deeply devoted — and you expect the same enduring reliability in return.",
	"7_Gemini":      "With the cusp of your Seventh House in Gemini, you are drawn to partners who are intellectually stimulating, communicative, and versatile. Your close relationships are animated by conversation, mental exchange, and the pleasure of a quick, engaged mind across from you. You need a partnership that keeps you mentally alive and a partner who is as curious about the world as you are.",
	"7_Cancer":      "With the cusp of your Seventh House in Cancer, you are drawn to partners who are emotionally nurturing, protective, and deeply invested in home and family. Your close relationships have a strong emotional and domestic quality — you seek a partnership that feels like home. You offer emotional depth and fierce loyalty, and you need a partner who can meet your emotional intensity with genuine care.",
	"7_Leo":         "With the cusp of your Seventh House in Leo, you are drawn to partners who are warm, creative, and self-expressive — people who bring genuine radiance and generosity to the relationship. You seek a partnership that has a quality of drama and romance, and you give lavishly in love. Recognition and appreciation within your partnerships are deeply important to you.",
	"7_Virgo":       "With the cusp of your Seventh House in Virgo, you are drawn to partners who are thoughtful, helpful, and attentive to detail. Your close relationships have a quality of mutual service and practical support — you show love through competent, considerate action. Your standards in partnership are high, and you are most at ease with someone who brings intelligence and genuine helpfulness to the relationship.",
	"7_Libra":       "With the cusp of your Seventh House in Libra, the house is in its natural sign — partnership is the area of life most naturally graced by Libra's qualities of beauty, diplomacy, and harmony. You seek a relationship characterized by balance, mutual respect, and aesthetic refinement. Close partnerships are among the most important and fulfilling dimensions of your life.",
	"7_Scorpio":     "With the cusp of your Seventh House in Scorpio, you are drawn to partners who are intense, psychologically complex, and capable of genuine depth. Your close relationships tend to be transformative and all-or-nothing — you cannot maintain surface-level connection in your closest bonds. The crises your partnerships produce are often the catalysts for your most significant personal growth.",
	"7_Sagittarius": "With the cusp of your Seventh House in Sagittarius, you are drawn to partners who are adventurous, philosophically expansive, and free-spirited. Your close relationships need to feel like an ongoing journey — a shared quest for meaning, growth, and new experience. You value freedom within partnership and may prefer relationships that allow both people to continue growing as individuals.",
	"7_Capricorn":   "With the cusp of your Seventh House in Capricorn, you approach partnership with seriousness, commitment, and a long-term view. You are drawn to partners who are reliable, ambitious, and willing to build something lasting together. Your partnerships tend to mature and deepen over time, and you take the responsibilities of committed relationship seriously.",
	"7_Aquarius":    "With the cusp of your Seventh House in Aquarius, you are drawn to partners who are intellectually independent, unconventional, and genuinely their own person. Your close relationships need to have room for both partners to maintain real individual freedom. You value intellectual equality and mutual respect for each other's originality above almost everything else in partnership.",
	"7_Pisces":      "With the cusp of your Seventh House in Pisces, you are drawn to partners who are compassionate, creative, and spiritually attuned. Your close relationships have a quality of deep emotional and spiritual merging — you love idealistically and with the full surrender of your heart. The challenge is maintaining discernment about who is truly worthy of your profound capacity for devotion.",

	// ── HOUSE 8 ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"8_Aries":       "With the cusp of your Eighth House in Aries, your encounters with transformation, shared resources, and depth are direct, fast, and often initiated by you rather than imposed from outside. You approach crisis and change with courage and initiative, and your regenerations tend to be rapid and decisive. Conflicts over shared resources may arise, but you face them head-on.",
	"8_Taurus":      "With the cusp of your Eighth House in Taurus, your encounters with transformation and shared resources are steady, deliberate, and often financially grounded. You may benefit materially through partnership, inheritance, or patient investment. Your transformations are slow but thorough — you do not change easily, but when you do, the change is permanent and deeply embodied.",
	"8_Gemini":      "With the cusp of your Eighth House in Gemini, your encounters with transformation and depth are colored by intellectual curiosity and the need to understand what is happening below the surface. You process profound experiences by analyzing and communicating about them. You may be drawn to research, investigation, or any field that requires exploring the hidden dimensions of information.",
	"8_Cancer":      "With the cusp of your Eighth House in Cancer, your encounters with transformation and shared resources are deeply emotional and rooted in family dynamics. Your most significant psychological transformations tend to emerge from your family history and early emotional experiences. You may benefit materially through family, and your deepest fears and strengths are connected to your emotional foundations.",
	"8_Leo":         "With the cusp of your Eighth House in Leo, your encounters with transformation and shared resources are dramatic, proud, and often connected to your creative identity. You may experience intense power dynamics in your closest relationships, and your transformations tend to involve a reassertion of who you are at your core. Generosity and pride are both strong forces in your relationship with shared resources.",
	"8_Virgo":       "With the cusp of your Eighth House in Virgo, your encounters with transformation and shared resources are characterized by careful analysis and a desire to understand and improve. You approach the depths methodically — you want to understand the mechanics of whatever you are transforming. Shared financial matters benefit from your practical, detail-oriented approach.",
	"8_Libra":       "With the cusp of your Eighth House in Libra, your encounters with transformation and shared resources are filtered through the lens of fairness, balance, and partnership. You seek equity in shared financial arrangements and may experience your most significant transformations through the dynamics of close relationships. The pursuit of genuine justice in intimate partnerships is a recurring theme.",
	"8_Scorpio":     "With the cusp of your Eighth House in Scorpio, the house is in its natural sign — your encounters with transformation, shared resources, and psychological depth are particularly intense, thorough, and potentially profoundly regenerative. You are not afraid of the dark, and your capacity to transform through crisis and loss is extraordinary. Power and control within intimate dynamics are significant recurring themes.",
	"8_Sagittarius": "With the cusp of your Eighth House in Sagittarius, your encounters with transformation and depth are infused with philosophical meaning and a search for larger purpose. Your most significant life crises tend to produce genuine wisdom and an expanded worldview rather than defeat. You may be drawn to philosophical or spiritual frameworks that help you make sense of loss, death, and radical change.",
	"8_Capricorn":   "With the cusp of your Eighth House in Capricorn, your encounters with transformation and shared resources are approached with seriousness, discipline, and a long-term view. You manage shared finances with careful authority, and your personal transformations are slow, structural, and deeply built into who you become over time.",
	"8_Aquarius":    "With the cusp of your Eighth House in Aquarius, your encounters with transformation and shared resources are sudden, electric, and often genuinely liberating. Your deepest transformations tend to arrive as revelations — sudden shifts in understanding that free you from old patterns. You may approach shared resources in unconventional ways, and your relationship with the depths of the psyche is intellectually as well as emotionally engaged.",
	"8_Pisces":      "With the cusp of your Eighth House in Pisces, your encounters with transformation and depth are characterized by spiritual sensitivity, emotional dissolution, and a tendency for the boundaries of self to be profoundly challenged. Your most significant transformations are spiritual as much as psychological — experiences of loss or crisis that ultimately bring you closer to something transcendent and universal.",

	// ── HOUSE 9 ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"9_Aries":       "With the cusp of your Ninth House in Aries, your philosophical and spiritual development is animated by directness, independence, and the drive to forge your own beliefs without external direction. You pursue truth boldly and may be drawn to the role of pioneer or advocate in your chosen philosophical or spiritual arena. Travel and adventure are personally meaningful forms of growth.",
	"9_Taurus":      "With the cusp of your Ninth House in Taurus, your philosophical and spiritual development is grounded, patient, and connected to the physical world. You build your beliefs slowly and with great deliberateness, and once formed they are enduring. Your sense of the sacred may be found in beauty, nature, and the sensory richness of the physical world.",
	"9_Gemini":      "With the cusp of your Ninth House in Gemini, your philosophical and spiritual development is animated by intellectual curiosity and an appetite for diverse ideas. You may find it difficult to commit to a single belief system — you prefer to collect perspectives and synthesize them into a personal philosophy that is always evolving. Teaching, writing, and intellectual exchange are forms of spiritual practice for you.",
	"9_Cancer":      "With the cusp of your Ninth House in Cancer, your philosophical and spiritual development is deeply connected to your emotional life, family history, and ancestral roots. Your beliefs are felt as much as thought, and your spiritual home may be found in traditions that honor memory, lineage, and the sacred dimensions of everyday life.",
	"9_Leo":         "With the cusp of your Ninth House in Leo, your philosophical and spiritual development is animated by a need for genuine inspiration and the desire to express your beliefs with creative conviction. You are drawn to traditions or philosophies that celebrate the individual soul and its creative journey. You may be a natural teacher or passionate communicator of the ideas you believe in.",
	"9_Virgo":       "With the cusp of your Ninth House in Virgo, your philosophical and spiritual development is characterized by discernment, careful analysis, and a preference for traditions that have practical application. You approach belief systems with a critical intelligence and are not easily satisfied by doctrine that cannot withstand scrutiny. Your spiritual practice tends to be methodical and improvement-oriented.",
	"9_Libra":       "With the cusp of your Ninth House in Libra, your philosophical and spiritual development is animated by the pursuit of justice, balance, and beauty. You are drawn to philosophical traditions that emphasize fairness, harmony, and the value of diverse perspectives. Long-distance relationships and cross-cultural encounters may be particularly important to your philosophical growth.",
	"9_Scorpio":     "With the cusp of your Ninth House in Scorpio, your philosophical and spiritual development is intense, investigative, and oriented toward the hidden dimensions of truth. You are not satisfied with surface-level answers and may be drawn to mystical, psychological, or occult traditions that acknowledge the full depth of human experience. Your beliefs, once formed, are held with extraordinary conviction.",
	"9_Sagittarius": "With the cusp of your Ninth House in Sagittarius, the house is in its natural sign — philosophy, higher education, travel, and spiritual seeking are areas of natural enthusiasm and good fortune. You are a natural student of life, and your optimism and conviction make you a compelling teacher and communicator of ideas. The world, for you, is genuinely inexhaustible.",
	"9_Capricorn":   "With the cusp of your Ninth House in Capricorn, your philosophical and spiritual development is serious, structured, and oriented toward traditions with real depth and earned authority. You approach belief systems with rigor and take seriously the traditions that have stood the test of time. Your beliefs are earned through long reflection and carry the weight of genuine experience.",
	"9_Aquarius":    "With the cusp of your Ninth House in Aquarius, your philosophical and spiritual development is progressive, unconventional, and oriented toward the future. You are drawn to ideas that challenge established orthodoxy and to belief systems that emphasize collective liberation and human possibility. Your philosophy is your own invention — a forward-looking synthesis that owes more to your vision than to any received tradition.",
	"9_Pisces":      "With the cusp of your Ninth House in Pisces, your philosophical and spiritual development is mystical, compassionate, and oriented toward unity and transcendence. You are drawn to spiritual traditions that emphasize the dissolution of the individual ego into something larger, and your experience of the sacred is profoundly personal and difficult to articulate in doctrinal terms. Dreams, art, and contemplative practice are genuine paths to wisdom for you.",

	// ── HOUSE 10 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"10_Aries":       "With the cusp of your Tenth House in Aries, your public life and career are characterized by initiative, independence, and the drive to be first or to forge a new path. You are at your professional best when leading, competing, or building something entirely new. Your public reputation is built on your boldness and your willingness to act without waiting for permission.",
	"10_Taurus":      "With the cusp of your Tenth House in Taurus, your public life and career are characterized by patience, reliability, and a long-term commitment to building something of lasting value. You are at your professional best when given the time and stability to develop your work without being rushed. Your public reputation is built on your dependability and the enduring quality of what you produce.",
	"10_Gemini":      "With the cusp of your Tenth House in Gemini, your public life and career are characterized by communication, intellectual versatility, and the ability to work across multiple domains. You are at your professional best when your work involves words, ideas, and the exchange of information. Your public reputation is built on your intelligence, adaptability, and communicative skill.",
	"10_Cancer":      "With the cusp of your Tenth House in Cancer, your public life and career are characterized by emotional intelligence, nurturing, and a capacity to create a sense of belonging in professional settings. You are at your professional best in roles that involve caring for others or building organizations that feel like a family. Your public reputation is built on your warmth, your protectiveness, and your genuine care.",
	"10_Leo":         "With the cusp of your Tenth House in Leo, your public life and career are characterized by creative leadership, self-expression, and a natural capacity for public presence. You are at your professional best when in a visible role that allows you to inspire and lead. Your public reputation tends to be warm, radiant, and memorable — people remember how you made them feel.",
	"10_Virgo":       "With the cusp of your Tenth House in Virgo, your public life and career are characterized by precision, service, and the mastery of a specific craft. You are at your professional best when your work requires careful analysis and high standards. Your public reputation is built on your reliability, your attention to detail, and your genuine commitment to doing things right.",
	"10_Libra":       "With the cusp of your Tenth House in Libra, your public life and career are characterized by diplomacy, aesthetic sensibility, and the ability to bring people and ideas into harmonious alignment. You are at your professional best in roles that involve mediation, design, or the cultivation of beauty and fairness. Your public reputation is built on your grace, your fairness, and your collaborative spirit.",
	"10_Scorpio":     "With the cusp of your Tenth House in Scorpio, your public life and career are characterized by depth, intensity, and a capacity to transform whatever field you enter. You are at your professional best in roles that involve investigation, the management of significant resources, or the navigation of complex power dynamics. Your public reputation carries a quality of formidable, quietly authoritative depth.",
	"10_Sagittarius": "With the cusp of your Tenth House in Sagittarius, your public life and career are characterized by vision, philosophical conviction, and a natural gift for inspiring others. You are at your professional best when your work involves the communication of ideas, the exploration of possibilities, or the building of something that points toward a larger horizon. Your public reputation is built on your enthusiasm, wisdom, and expansive spirit.",
	"10_Capricorn":   "With the cusp of your Tenth House in Capricorn, the house is in its natural sign — your public life and career are characterized by ambition, discipline, and the patient, long-term building of real authority. You take your professional life seriously and hold yourself to high standards. Your public reputation is built over time through sustained competence and deepens with age.",
	"10_Aquarius":    "With the cusp of your Tenth House in Aquarius, your public life and career are characterized by originality, innovation, and a commitment to progressive ideals. You are at your professional best when your work involves disrupting old systems or building something genuinely new. Your public reputation is built on your intellectual independence, your forward thinking, and your commitment to a larger collective vision.",
	"10_Pisces":      "With the cusp of your Tenth House in Pisces, your public life and career are characterized by imagination, compassion, and a quality of spiritual or artistic depth. You are at your professional best in roles that involve healing, artistic creation, or service that transcends purely practical concerns. Your public reputation has an idealistic or otherworldly quality that is difficult to define but unmistakable.",

	// ── HOUSE 11 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"11_Aries":       "With the cusp of your Eleventh House in Aries, your social life, communities, and collective pursuits are animated by initiative, independence, and competitive energy. You are a natural catalyst in group settings — often the person who gets things started. Your friendships tend to be with energetic, assertive individuals, and your social goals are pursued with the same directness you bring to personal ambitions.",
	"11_Taurus":      "With the cusp of your Eleventh House in Taurus, your social life, communities, and collective pursuits are characterized by loyalty, stability, and a preference for long-standing, reliable connections. You build your social network slowly and with great care, and the friendships you form tend to be enduring. Your collective goals are oriented toward material and aesthetic abundance that can be shared and sustained.",
	"11_Gemini":      "With the cusp of your Eleventh House in Gemini, your social life, communities, and collective pursuits are animated by intellectual exchange, communication, and variety. You are most at home in diverse, stimulating social networks, and your friendships tend to be formed through shared curiosity and the pleasure of lively, wide-ranging conversation.",
	"11_Cancer":      "With the cusp of your Eleventh House in Cancer, your social life, communities, and collective pursuits are characterized by emotional warmth, nurturing, and a need for genuine belonging. Your friendships have a family-like quality — you care for the people in your network with the same protective intensity you bring to your closest personal bonds.",
	"11_Leo":         "With the cusp of your Eleventh House in Leo, your social life, communities, and collective pursuits are animated by warmth, creativity, and a natural capacity for group leadership. You bring genuine radiance to your social networks and tend to attract a wide circle of admirers and friends. Your collective goals often involve creating something — a community, a creative movement — where individual gifts can shine together.",
	"11_Virgo":       "With the cusp of your Eleventh House in Virgo, your social life, communities, and collective pursuits are characterized by discernment, practicality, and a desire to be genuinely useful to the groups you belong to. You may have fewer but more carefully chosen friendships, and your participation in collective endeavors tends to be defined by the quality of your contribution rather than the size of your presence.",
	"11_Libra":       "With the cusp of your Eleventh House in Libra, your social life, communities, and collective pursuits are characterized by diplomacy, aesthetic sensitivity, and a gift for bringing diverse people into harmonious connection. You are naturally skilled at building and maintaining networks, and your friendships tend to be gracious and mutually enriching.",
	"11_Scorpio":     "With the cusp of your Eleventh House in Scorpio, your social life, communities, and collective pursuits are characterized by depth, intensity, and a preference for genuine, transformative connection over casual socializing. You may have few but profoundly meaningful friendships, and the communities you are part of tend to be oriented toward radical change or deep collective exploration.",
	"11_Sagittarius": "With the cusp of your Eleventh House in Sagittarius, your social life, communities, and collective pursuits are animated by philosophical enthusiasm, a love of freedom, and the desire to expand into the world alongside others who share your appetite for growth. Your friendships tend to be with adventurous, philosophically oriented individuals, and your collective goals are broad and visionary.",
	"11_Capricorn":   "With the cusp of your Eleventh House in Capricorn, your social life, communities, and collective pursuits are characterized by seriousness, ambition, and a preference for connections that are mutually productive as well as personally meaningful. Your friendships tend to be with accomplished, responsible individuals, and your participation in collective endeavors is defined by reliability and long-term commitment.",
	"11_Aquarius":    "With the cusp of your Eleventh House in Aquarius, the house is in its natural sign — your social life, communities, and collective pursuits are naturally vibrant, original, and oriented toward the future. You are drawn to groups that are pushing boundaries and to friends who are genuinely unusual and intellectually free. Your collective goals are humanitarian, visionary, and ahead of their time.",
	"11_Pisces":      "With the cusp of your Eleventh House in Pisces, your social life, communities, and collective pursuits are characterized by idealism, compassion, and a longing for spiritual connection within your social world. Your friendships may have a soulmate-like quality, and the communities you are drawn to tend to have an artistic, healing, or spiritual mission. Your collective goals are infused with a desire to dissolve barriers and create something universal.",

	// ── HOUSE 12 ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"12_Aries":       "With the cusp of your Twelfth House in Aries, your hidden self and unconscious life are animated by assertiveness, anger, and a drive for independence that you may not always feel free to express directly. Your most significant inner work involves learning to claim your own desire and initiative without fear or guilt. Hidden courage — the willingness to act on what you truly want — is your deepest resource.",
	"12_Taurus":      "With the cusp of your Twelfth House in Taurus, your hidden self and unconscious life are animated by a deep, sometimes unacknowledged need for sensory comfort, stability, and beauty. You may carry fears around material scarcity or self-worth that operate below the level of conscious awareness. Your deepest restoration comes from physical beauty, nature, and the patient enjoyment of the senses.",
	"12_Gemini":      "With the cusp of your Twelfth House in Gemini, your hidden self and unconscious life are animated by a rich, often unvoiced inner conversation. You may carry unspoken thoughts, unfinished mental processes, or a private intellectual life that you rarely share. Your deepest insights often arrive as sudden mental clarity — an inner voice that knows more than your conscious mind is willing to say.",
	"12_Cancer":      "With the cusp of your Twelfth House in Cancer, your hidden self and unconscious life are animated by deep emotional memories, family patterns, and a longing for nurturing that you may carry invisibly. Your most significant inner work involves understanding the emotional inheritance you carry from your family of origin. Solitude and emotional rest are genuinely restorative, not self-indulgent, for you.",
	"12_Leo":         "With the cusp of your Twelfth House in Leo, your hidden self and unconscious life are animated by a creative and expressive force that you may not fully claim in public. There may be a tension between your desire for recognition and a deeper pull toward invisibility or privacy. Your most significant inner work involves allowing your genuine creative gifts to be seen without the fear of exposure or loss.",
	"12_Virgo":       "With the cusp of your Twelfth House in Virgo, your hidden self and unconscious life are animated by a highly critical inner voice that holds you to standards you may not even consciously recognize. Your most significant inner work involves developing compassion for your own imperfections and learning to release the need for self-improvement as a condition of self-worth.",
	"12_Libra":       "With the cusp of your Twelfth House in Libra, your hidden self and unconscious life are animated by a longing for perfect harmony and a deep fear of conflict or rupture in your relationships. You may carry unresolved relational grief or an invisible need for beauty and balance that shapes your choices without your fully knowing it. Your deepest restoration comes through beauty, art, and the quiet cultivation of inner peace.",
	"12_Scorpio":     "With the cusp of your Twelfth House in Scorpio, your hidden self and unconscious life are animated by the full, unfiltered depths of Scorpio's power — intense emotions, unconscious compulsions, and a capacity for regeneration that you may not yet have fully claimed. Your most significant inner work is not avoidance but descent: willingly entering the depths of your own psyche and transforming what you find there.",
	"12_Sagittarius": "With the cusp of your Twelfth House in Sagittarius, your hidden self and unconscious life are animated by philosophical searching, unexpressed beliefs, and a spiritual hunger that may not have a public outlet. You may carry a private faith or philosophical conviction that runs deeper than what you reveal to the world. Your most significant inner work involves trusting your own vision enough to live by it openly.",
	"12_Capricorn":   "With the cusp of your Twelfth House in Capricorn, your hidden self and unconscious life are animated by deep-seated fears around failure, inadequacy, or the weight of unfinished responsibilities. Your most significant inner work involves confronting the inner judge — the relentless voice of discipline and self-demand — and developing genuine self-compassion alongside your considerable drive.",
	"12_Aquarius":    "With the cusp of your Twelfth House in Aquarius, your hidden self and unconscious life are animated by a visionary, future-oriented intelligence that may not always find easy expression in the present. You may carry unspoken ideals, a private sense of being ahead of your time, or an unconventional inner life that you rarely share. Your deepest restoration comes through solitude, intellectual freedom, and work that serves a vision larger than yourself.",
	"12_Pisces":      "With the cusp of your Twelfth House in Pisces, the house is in its natural sign — your hidden self and unconscious life are infused with Neptune's qualities of spiritual depth, dissolving boundaries, and extraordinary compassion. You carry an unusually permeable inner world, and the unconscious is a genuine, living reality for you. Your deepest restoration comes through spiritual practice, creative surrender, and the willingness to release what cannot be held.",
}
